      <section eId="sec_215_45">
        <num>215.45</num>
        <heading>Compounding a crime</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_215_45__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>He solicits, accepts or agrees to accept any benefit upon an\nagreement or understanding that he will refrain from initiating a\nprosecution for a crime; or\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_215_45__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>He confers, or offers or agrees to confer, any benefit upon\nanother person upon an agreement or understanding that such other person\nwill refrain from initiating a prosecution for a crime.\n  2. In any prosecution under this section, it is an affirmative defense\nthat the benefit did not exceed an amount which the defendant reasonably\nbelieved to be due as restitution or indemnification for harm caused by\nthe crime.\n  Compounding a crime is a class A misdemeanor.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
